description: Primes not of form | 3^a +- 2^b | where a, b are nonnegative integers.
references: N. J. A. Sloane and Simon Plouffe, The Encyclopedia of Integer Sequences, Academic Press, 1995 (includes this sequence).
example: 127 = 2^7 - 3^0, so 127 is not a member.257 = 3^0 + 2^8, so 257 is not a member.
author: _N. J. A. Sloane_, _Mira Bernstein_, _Robert G. Wilson v_
extensions: Minor edits by _N. J. A. Sloane_, Jun 27 2010
More terms from _Jon E. Schoenfield_, Jun 30 2010
